  }
}

{
  "jurisdiction": "PH",
  "section_id": "190",
  "title": ". Rehabilitation services. ",
  "content": ". Rehabilitation services. \na. The System shall, as soon as practicable, establish a continuing program, for the rehabilitation of \ninjured and handicapped employees who shall be entitled to rehabilitation services, which shall \nconsist of medical, surgical or hospital treatment, including appliances if they have been \nhandicapped by the injury, to help them become physically independent. \n   \nb. As soon as practicable, the System shall establish centers equipped and staffed to provide a \nbalanced program of remedial treatment, vocational assessment and preparation designed to meet \nthe individual needs of each handicapped employee to restore him to suitable employment, \nincluding assistance as may be within its resources, to help each rehabilitee to develop his mental, \nvocational or social potential.  \nChapter VI \nDISABILITY BENEFITS",
  "is_repealed": false,
  "metadata": {
    "source_file": "Labor-Code-of-the-Philippines-DOLE.pdf",
    "jurisdiction": "PH",
    "corpus_category": "general",
