{
  "jurisdiction": "PH",
  "section_id": "103",
  "title": ". Time of payment. Wages shall be paid at least once every two (2) weeks or twice a month at ",
  "content": ". Time of payment. Wages shall be paid at least once every two (2) weeks or twice a month at \nintervals not exceeding sixteen (16) days. If on account of force majeure or circumstances beyond the \nemployer’s control, payment of wages on or within the time herein provided cannot be made, the employer \nshall pay the wages immediately after such force majeure or circumstances have ceased. No employer shall \nmake payment with less frequency than once a month. \nThe payment of wages of employees engaged to perform a task which cannot be completed in two (2) weeks \nshall be subject to the following conditions, in the absence of a collective bargaining agreement or arbitration \naward: \n1. That payments are made at intervals not exceeding sixteen (16) days, in proportion to the amount of \nwork completed; \n   \n2. That final settlement is made upon completion of the work.",
  "is_repealed": false,
  "metadata": {
    "source_file": "Labor-Code-of-the-Philippines-DOLE.pdf",
    "jurisdiction": "PH",
    "corpus_category": "wages",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-21T14:28:37.573266"
  }
}

{
  "jurisdiction": "PH",
  "section_id": "102",
  "title": ". Forms of payment. No employer shall pay the wages of an employee by means of promissory ",
  "content": ". Forms of payment. No employer shall pay the wages of an employee by means of promissory \nnotes, vouchers, coupons, tokens, tickets, chits, or any object other than legal tender, even when expressly \nrequested by the employee. \nPayment of wages by check or money order shall be allowed when such manner of payment is customary on \nthe date of effectivity of this Code, or is necessary because of special circumstances as specified in \nappropriate regulations to be issued by the Secretary of Labor and Employment or as stipulated in a collective \nbargaining agreement.",
